);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

Context('Numeric');

$n = random(4,5,1);

$a = random(2,10,1);
$k = random(2,9,1);
if ($k == $a) { 
	$k=$k+1;
}

@which = ('first', 'second', 'third', 'fourth');
$tag1 = random(0,1,1);
$tag2 = random($tag1+1,3,1);
 
BEGIN_TEXT

If the determinant of a \($n \times $n\) matrix \(A\) is \(\det(A)=$a\), and the matrix \(D\) is obtained from \(A\) by
adding \($k\) times the $which[$tag2] row to the $which[$tag1], then 
$BR
$BR 
\(\det(D)= \) \{ans_rule(10)\}.  

END_TEXT

ANS(Compute($a)->cmp);
